title: Everything Secretary of State Antony Blinken Has Said About the Israel-Hamas War
description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken has been walking a diplomatic tightrope as Israel faces growing public pressure to call for a ceasefire.

title: Netanyahu Discusses Hamas Assault, Gaza’s Future, and Potential Hostage Deal on Meet the Press
description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu appeared on NBC’s Meet the Press to discuss Israel's war on Hamas in Gaza.

title: Russia Ramps Up Attacks on Key cities in Eastern Ukraine
description: Russian forces have ramped up attacks in eastern Ukraine in an attempt to gain ground, Ukrainian military officials said.

title: Floods Kill at Least 31 in Somalia as U.N. Releases $25 Million Humanitarian Aid Package
description: Since October, floods have reportedly displaced nearly half a million people and disrupted the lives of over 1.2 million people.

title: Fighting Rages Near Gaza’s Main Hospital as Netanyahu Rejects Ceasefire Calls
description: In a televised address on Saturday, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu rejected growing international calls for a cease-fire unless it includes the release of all the nearly 240 hostages captured by Hamas in the Oct. 7 rampage.

title: How Mayor Oh Se-hoon Is Using K-Culture to Make Seoul a Business Hub
description: Seoul's mayor spoke to TIME about his tourism strategy and why South Korea needs nuclear weapons.
